wedding. Read below \u21f2\\n[\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcf\ud835\uddbe \ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc1\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcc \ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddcd \ud835\uddbf\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcb \ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc7\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcb\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddc7]\\n\\n\ud835\udde0\ud835\ude06 \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nDressing for summer weddings can be tricky. Aside from being the most popular time for nuptials, it tends to be quite hot, which means the dark thick woolen 3 piece may not be the best choice. \\n\\nFirst thing first though: always check the invitation for the dress code. If there is none, reach out to the couple to ask. If you\u2019re unsure, it\u2019s a good rule of thumb to never dress up more than the groom. \\n\\nIf the dress code is anything similar to \u201clounge suit\u201d, \u201csummer smart\u201d, or \u201ccocktail attire\u201d, I would highly recommend a linen suit, preferably in Irish linen as it wrinkles less (as worn here). You could also go bolder with a seersucker. \\nNow, some traditionalists may take offense to the linen suit, but the above mentioned dress codes allows you to play around with both lighter textures and colors. \\n\\nMy outfit here is slightly on the more formal side of the casual spectrum, as it features both black oxfords and French cuffs. You could easily swap out the shoes for a brown lace up, or why not a loafer. Just make sure to always wear socks for a wedding. \\n\\nI\u2019ve played around a bit with the tie here, going with a bolder floral print, as opposed to a solid colored grenadine tie and pocket square. \\n\\nStick to the dress code, but let your personality shine where allowed! And always make sure the fit is on point. If you bought an off the rack suit, taking it to a tailor for some minor alterations is highly recommended. \\n\\n\ud835\uddec\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddff \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat are your tips for attending a summer wedding?\\n\\nLet me know in the comments below They are both softer and less stiff, which makes them ideal for a more casual pairing, such as this one. \\n\\nPaired with Belgian tassels and garoupe linen shirt. \\n\\nI must say, these type of relaxed outfits are some of my absolute favorites. fabrics: part 4 - fresco.  Read below \u21f2\\n[\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcf\ud835\uddbe \ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc1\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcc \ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddcd \ud835\uddbf\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcb \ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc7\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcb\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddc7]\\n\\n\ud835\udde0\ud835\ude06 \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat is Fresco\/high twist wool? Fresco, at this point, is almost interchangeable with the generic term high twist wool. You\u2019ll see other high twist wool fabrics referred to as fresco, although the name belongs to the mill Huddersfield. Other notable examples of high twist wool is Crispaire (Holland \\u0026 Sherry) and Fox Air (Fox Brothers).\\n\\nHigh twist wool is woven from strands of yarn that are woven tighter together than otherwise. The result is a more breathable, open weave fabric that is incredibly resistant to wrinkling. The wrinkle resistant properties makes it an excellent fabric for travel. It also allows the fabric to keep that newly pressed look for quite some time. \\nFurthermore, the fabric is less prone to create shiny areas, such as other wools may develop with use. \\n\\nThe downside is that it\u2019s not as soft to the touch as \u201cregular\u201d (like the super 120 etc) wool, but rather feels a bit coarse. However, this also makes the cloth a lot more durable. \\n\\nDepending on the weight of the fabric, you can easily extend the use into early spring and late fall. Or if you want to be a bit of a rebel, like me, you can even wear it in winter (thick knit and woolen OTC socks when it\u2019s mild). \\n\\n\ud835\uddec\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddff \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat are your thoughts on high twist wool? \\n\\nLet me know in the comments below \ud83d\udc47 \\n\\nIf you like this, and other versions of both classical and casual sartorial outfits, be sure to hit follow!\\n\\n\ud835\udddb\ud835\uddee\ud835\ude00\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\uddee\ud835\uddf4\ud835\ude00\\n#mensweardaily #sartorialstyle #rakish #mnswr #ootdmen #moderngentleman #styleforum However, those are far from the only options for you to wear. \\n\\nWhen inspiration runs short, and you\u2019re looking for different color palette, you don\u2019t need to look further than to the nature around you. \\n\\nWhen looking to nature, you\u2019ll find a myriad of different hues that you can use to create different outfits. \\n\\nTo some, earthy colors may come off as boring or uninspiring, but they definitely don\u2019t have to be. The textures and cut of your garments will - as always - make or break the look. \\nThe benefit of lower contrast earth tones is that they will work with all skin tones. \\n\\nAs far as which tones fit into the earth palette, you\u2019ve got your browns, but you also have blue and green. Yellow, red, \\u0026 orange (imagine the leaves of an autumn tree against the bark). wedding. Read below \u21f2\\n[\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcf\ud835\uddbe \ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc1\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcc \ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddcd \ud835\uddbf\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcb \ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc7\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcb\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddc7]\\n\\n\ud835\udde0\ud835\ude06 \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nDressing for summer weddings can be tricky. Aside from being the most popular time for nuptials, it tends to be quite hot, which means the dark thick woolen 3 piece may not be the best choice. \\n\\nFirst thing first though: always check the invitation for the dress code. If there is none, reach out to the couple to ask. If you\u2019re unsure, it\u2019s a good rule of thumb to never dress up more than the groom. \\n\\nIf the dress code is anything similar to \u201clounge suit\u201d, \u201csummer smart\u201d, or \u201ccocktail attire\u201d, I would highly recommend a linen suit, preferably in Irish linen as it wrinkles less (as worn here). You could also go bolder with a seersucker. \\nNow, some traditionalists may take offense to the linen suit, but the above mentioned dress codes allows you to play around with both lighter textures and colors. \\n\\nMy outfit here is slightly on the more formal side of the casual spectrum, as it features both black oxfords and French cuffs. You could easily swap out the shoes for a brown lace up, or why not a loafer. Just make sure to always wear socks for a wedding. \\n\\nI\u2019ve played around a bit with the tie here, going with a bolder floral print, as opposed to a solid colored grenadine tie and pocket square. \\n\\nStick to the dress code, but let your personality shine where allowed! And always make sure the fit is on point. If you bought an off the rack suit, taking it to a tailor for some minor alterations is highly recommended. \\n\\n\ud835\uddec\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddff \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat are your tips for attending a summer wedding?\\n\\nLet me know in the comments below week and it reminded me of this floral tie that I bought for their wedding, with the theme \u201cfloral\u201d. At the time I wore it with my own wedding suit: a slightly darker royal blue super 130 wool suit. \\nUnfortunately, that suit doesn\u2019t really fit my aesthetic anymore. The trousers are too short and a bit too slim, even though I\u2019ve taken them out a bit. \\n\\nBut here I\u2019ve paired it with beige linen suit instead. A slightly more formal pairing overall with French cuffs and black oxfords. You could, however, argue that the color of the suit and the linen is not formal enough, but for a summer wedding it is perfect. The pocket square could also be swapped for a president fold in white, but we are already having fun with the tie, so why not go a bit more bold. I\u2019ll write more about my thoughts in the upcoming reel, so keep an eye out for that. \\n\\nVacation update:\\nYesterday was spent driving most of the day. We hit some snags in our plans, which meant we didn\u2019t really have time to do the things we had planned to do in LA. \\nWe did a quick drive thru on Rodeo Drive, just to have seen it, as well as a stop by Venice beach. The rest of the time was spent driving. Highway 1 between LA and SFO was beautiful, especially during sunset. However, we didn\u2019t arrive back in SFO until 02:30. We have a few more days here until we head over to NYC. \\n\\nSwipe thru for detail photos \ud83d\udc49\\n\\n\ud835\uddec\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddff fabrics: part 4 - fresco.  Read below \u21f2\\n[\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcf\ud835\uddbe \ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc1\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcc \ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddcd \ud835\uddbf\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddcb \ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc7\ud835\uddcc\ud835\uddc9\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddcb\ud835\uddba\ud835\uddcd\ud835\uddc2\ud835\uddc8\ud835\uddc7]\\n\\n\ud835\udde0\ud835\ude06 \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat is Fresco\/high twist wool? Fresco, at this point, is almost interchangeable with the generic term high twist wool. You\u2019ll see other high twist wool fabrics referred to as fresco, although the name belongs to the mill Huddersfield. Other notable examples of high twist wool is Crispaire (Holland \\u0026 Sherry) and Fox Air (Fox Brothers).\\n\\nHigh twist wool is woven from strands of yarn that are woven tighter together than otherwise. The result is a more breathable, open weave fabric that is incredibly resistant to wrinkling. The wrinkle resistant properties makes it an excellent fabric for travel. It also allows the fabric to keep that newly pressed look for quite some time. \\nFurthermore, the fabric is less prone to create shiny areas, such as other wools may develop with use. \\n\\nThe downside is that it\u2019s not as soft to the touch as \u201cregular\u201d (like the super 120 etc) wool, but rather feels a bit coarse. However, this also makes the cloth a lot more durable. \\n\\nDepending on the weight of the fabric, you can easily extend the use into early spring and late fall. Or if you want to be a bit of a rebel, like me, you can even wear it in winter (thick knit and woolen OTC socks when it\u2019s mild). \\n\\n\ud835\uddec\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddff \ud835\ude01\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfc\ud835\ude02\ud835\uddf4\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\ude00\\nWhat are your thoughts on high twist wool? \\n\\nLet me know in the comments below \ud83d\udc47 \\n\\nIf you like this, and other versions of both classical and casual sartorial outfits, be sure to hit follow!\\n\\n\ud835\udddb\ud835\uddee\ud835\ude00\ud835\uddf5\ud835\ude01\ud835\uddee\ud835\uddf4\ud835\ude00\\n#mensweardaily #sartorialstyle #rakish #mnswr #ootdmen #moderngentleman #styleforum
